15:46.571 --> 15:47.779
Dump him.

15:47.989 --> 15:51.617
Let's get rid of Number 4, 6,
and I'd say lose Number 12...

15:51.784 --> 15:54.161
but the prosecutor will fuck up
and do it for us.

15:54.370 --> 15:55.829
Number 6?

15:59.000 --> 16:01.293
You're kidding, right?
She's my first choice.

16:01.502 --> 16:02.961
She's my first pass.

16:03.129 --> 16:04.921
And 4?

16:08.009 --> 16:10.761
With the dreadlocks? That's crazy.

16:10.970 --> 16:14.514
- That's a defendant's juror.
- Did you see his shoes?

16:15.391 --> 16:19.728
Look, kid, maybe down in Florida
you are the next big thing.

16:19.937 --> 16:23.106
This is New York.
We're not squeezing oranges here.

16:23.316 --> 16:27.653
He polishes those shoes every night.
He makes his own clothes.

16:27.820 --> 16:32.908
He looks like a brother with an attitude,
but I see a man with a gun under his bed.

16:33.076 --> 16:36.036
And woe betide the creature
who steps into his garden.

16:36.204 --> 16:37.913
Number 6...

16:38.081 --> 16:39.581
your favorite...

16:39.791 --> 16:41.917
she's damaged goods.

16:42.085 --> 16:45.295
She's a Catholic schoolteacher, hmm?

16:45.463 --> 16:47.214
Believes in human frailty...

16:47.423 --> 16:49.758
No. Something's missing from her.

16:49.926 --> 16:51.468
She's wrong.

16:51.636 --> 16:53.595
She wants on this jury.

16:53.763 --> 16:56.598
Somebody hurt her
and she wants revenge.

16:58.601 --> 17:00.852
How the hell do you know that?

17:01.771 --> 17:02.979
I don't know.

17:04.732 --> 17:08.652
Either you put a stop
to this happy horseshit or I walk.

17:09.153 --> 17:10.612
Walk.

17:12.865 --> 17:16.910
Here's the deal: If I lose with your jury,
you do the explaining.

17:17.369 --> 17:19.079
Your Honor, may I continue?

17:19.247 --> 17:22.749
We'd like to excuse
Jurors 3, 4 and 6.

18:14.761 --> 18:17.220
Hi. You're home early for a change.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.264
I just happened to find out...

18:19.432 --> 18:21.683
I was pregnant on the same day
that I got the show.

18:21.851 --> 18:23.351
Your mother called.

18:23.936 --> 18:26.354
She has her bad feeling.

18:30.860 --> 18:32.986
Every now and then, she gets one right.

18:36.032 --> 18:37.824
You okay?

18:40.036 --> 18:41.828
Something's up.

18:41.996 --> 18:45.165
They deliberated for 38 minutes.

18:48.211 --> 18:49.711
Kevin.

18:49.879 --> 18:51.963
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.

18:54.467 --> 18:58.845
What the hell did they expect?
The man is as guilty as can be.

18:59.013 --> 19:02.265
Wasn't a jury anywhere gonna let him off.

19:02.725 --> 19:04.392
Yeah.

19:05.895 --> 19:07.395
Except one.

19:07.563 --> 19:09.105
What?

19:11.734 --> 19:12.943
Kev.

19:14.320 --> 19:16.404
Not fucking guilty!

19:16.572 --> 19:20.242
- Oh, my God. You lying sack of shit.
- Ha, ha.

19:20.409 --> 19:22.327
Thirty-eight minutes, my jury.

19:23.704 --> 19:24.913
Yes!

19:25.081 --> 19:27.457
Thirty-eight minutes.

19:27.625 --> 19:30.752
- You did it!
- My jury. I'm too good.

19:33.673 --> 19:36.258
- Glad you could stick around.
- It's your dime.

19:36.467 --> 19:37.676
Sorry to keep you waiting.

19:37.885 --> 19:41.137
Mr. Milton got pinned down in Indonesia
longer than expected.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.473
Good morning, Caprice.

19:43.641 --> 19:45.183
Good morning, Mr. Heath.

19:45.393 --> 19:46.643
Your messages.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.607
Not bad?

19:52.942 --> 19:54.693
You can play it cool if you want...

19:54.861 --> 19:57.863
but when I first walked in,
my jaw was on the floor.

19:59.866 --> 20:00.907
Thank you.

20:01.242 --> 20:04.327
This is our home office.
We have many international arrangements...

20:04.495 --> 20:07.497
so Mr. Milton spends a great deal
of his time in the air.

20:07.665 --> 20:10.500
- Three o'clock, we got the Greeks.
- Am I good cop or bad cop?

20:10.668 --> 20:12.168
We may not need a good cop.

20:12.378 --> 20:13.920
Oh, I love it.

20:14.088 --> 20:18.133
In addition to our corporate clients
we're representing 25 foreign countries:

20:18.342 --> 20:21.303
The Mideast, the Balkans,
Central America, West Africa...

20:21.512 --> 20:24.514
Interesting work, but travel-intensive.

21:19.528 --> 21:20.695
Behind you.

21:22.281 --> 21:23.323
I'm sorry.

21:23.532 --> 21:25.909
Please. Kevin Lomax.

21:26.077 --> 21:28.328
- John Milton.
- Nice to meet you.

21:34.043 --> 21:35.669
So?

21:35.836 --> 21:37.712
Have we been treating you well?

21:37.922 --> 21:39.297
Very well, thank you.

21:39.465 --> 21:41.466
And your wife, she had a good time?

21:41.634 --> 21:45.637
She sure has. It's been great.
The whole thing's been great.

21:47.598 --> 21:48.682
That's our secret:

21:48.849 --> 21:50.475
Kill you with kindness.

21:53.396 --> 21:55.313
What's your secret?

21:55.481 --> 21:57.482
I couldn't say.

21:57.650 --> 21:58.942
You were a prosecutor.

21:59.110 --> 22:02.862
Out of law school.
Five years in the Jacksonville DA's office.

22:04.699 --> 22:07.617
Sixty-four straight convictions.

22:08.995 --> 22:10.704
What a number.

22:10.871 --> 22:12.622
I like to be in court.

22:12.790 --> 22:14.833
I didn't plea out a lot.

22:15.418 --> 22:16.459
What's that like?

22:16.627 --> 22:19.129
One day you put them away,
the next you set them free.

22:20.756 --> 22:22.465
Takes a little getting used to.

22:22.633 --> 22:26.011
- Pays better, though, doesn't it?
- Yes, it does.

22:27.221 --> 22:32.642
That math teacher, the Gettys case.
Now, I hear you were brilliant.

22:32.810 --> 22:34.310
Prosecutor dropped the ball.

22:34.478 --> 22:36.104
Really?

22:36.355 --> 22:37.939
You think your guy was guilty?

22:38.149 --> 22:39.190
I didn't say that.

22:39.400 --> 22:40.775
What'd you say?

22:42.361 --> 22:43.653
How's this:

22:43.821 --> 22:47.032
I began the case with a clear conscience.

22:54.331 --> 22:55.915
I was sure you had a secret.

22:59.795 --> 23:01.129
The men's room.

23:01.297 --> 23:03.798
Upstairs men's room
in the Duval County courthouse.

23:03.966 --> 23:06.593
There's a hole in the wall
to the next room.

23:06.761 --> 23:09.220
I spent five years listening
to juries deliberate.

23:09.722 --> 23:11.598
- I love it.
- Love it all you want.

23:11.766 --> 23:13.058
Just don't repeat it.

23:13.225 --> 23:16.269
I'm not sure the Florida Bar Association
would appreciate it.

23:16.437 --> 23:18.688
My lips are sealed.

23:18.856 --> 23:22.275
You don't really want to go back
to Florida, do you?

23:26.322 --> 23:28.073
Walk with me.

23:48.219 --> 23:50.011
What do you think?

23:50.763 --> 23:53.014
Some people can't handle it.

23:54.308 --> 23:56.017
It's peaceful.

23:56.852 --> 23:59.062
My sentiments exactly.

23:59.230 --> 24:05.110
Ha, ha. So fill in the résumé for me.
Tell me... your father, what does he do?

24:05.277 --> 24:08.905
I never got to know my father.
He passed away before I was born.

24:09.073 --> 24:11.491
My mother raised me. Just the two of us.

24:11.700 --> 24:15.411
- She never remarried?
- She wasn't married the first time.

24:15.579 --> 24:19.624
That can't be easy in a town
like Gainesville, can it?

24:19.792 --> 24:22.252
I don't think it's easy anywhere.

24:24.130 --> 24:25.505
Holy shit.

24:25.673 --> 24:28.716
Different when you're looking down,
isn't it?

24:28.884 --> 24:30.802
Yes, it is.

24:31.554 --> 24:33.138
Oh, my God.

24:33.305 --> 24:34.722
Your mother...

24:34.890 --> 24:36.641
what's she like?

24:36.809 --> 24:39.853
She's a preacher's daughter.
She's tough.

24:40.020 --> 24:43.648
She's worked in a poultry plant
for as long as I can remember.

24:43.816 --> 24:47.527
She's got a church she really likes,
so she's usually there or they go out.

24:47.695 --> 24:49.571
They do a lot of volunteer work.

24:49.738 --> 24:53.449
Behold, I send you out
as sheep amidst the wolves.

24:54.994 --> 24:56.703
So they say.

24:56.871 --> 24:58.288
It didn't rub off?

24:58.455 --> 25:00.331
The Book? The Church?

25:00.499 --> 25:02.125
No, I'm on parole.

25:02.293 --> 25:05.587
Early release for time served.

25:08.382 --> 25:11.050
A lot of potential clients down there.

25:11.218 --> 25:12.719
Are we negotiating?

25:13.846 --> 25:15.096
Always.

25:16.557 --> 25:18.892
Can I ask you a question, then?

25:19.268 --> 25:22.103
Why do you need a criminal department?

25:22.271 --> 25:26.649
Our clients break the law
like anyone else.

25:29.403 --> 25:33.198
I'm just tired of sending their business
across the street.

25:33.365 --> 25:37.035
- Are you offering me a job?
- I'm thinking about it.

25:37.953 --> 25:41.956
I know you've got talent.
I knew that before you got here.

25:42.124 --> 25:45.460
It's just the other thing I wonder about.

25:47.046 --> 25:48.838
What thing is that?

25:49.840 --> 25:50.965
Pressure.

25:52.218 --> 25:54.385
It changes everything. Pressure.

25:54.553 --> 25:57.931
Some people, you squeeze them,
they focus.

25:58.098 --> 26:00.225
Others fold.

26:01.977 --> 26:04.562
Can you summon your talent at will?

26:04.939 --> 26:07.440
Can you deliver on a deadline?

26:08.108 --> 26:09.943
Can you sleep at night?

26:11.695 --> 26:13.321
When do we talk about money?

26:13.489 --> 26:14.530
Money?

26:16.867 --> 26:18.368
Yeah.

26:18.535 --> 26:20.453
That's the easy part.

26:21.163 --> 26:23.623
They call this part of Fifth Avenue,
Carnegie Hill.

26:23.791 --> 26:26.376
Got the park right across the street,
and the reservoir.

26:26.543 --> 26:29.754
Best jogging in New York.
Mount Sinai Hospital is up the street.

26:29.922 --> 26:32.090
Some excellent schools.

26:32.258 --> 26:35.385
Not on the top of Mr. Milton's list
when he bought this building...

26:35.552 --> 26:37.553
but great neighborhood
for children.

26:37.721 --> 26:40.014
Great building.

26:40.224 --> 26:42.642
Follow the money all the way to the top.

26:42.851 --> 26:46.145
You got the managing director,
Eddie Barzoon, on 16.

26:46.355 --> 26:49.774
And, of course, Mr. Milton has the tower.

26:52.361 --> 26:54.404
- You must be Mary Ann.
- Yes, I am.

26:54.571 --> 26:57.448
Welcome. I'm Jackie Heath.

26:57.908 --> 26:59.826
It's nice of you to come by.

26:59.994 --> 27:02.161
Oh, please. We live across the hall.

27:02.329 --> 27:04.539
- You're kidding.
- Right there.

27:04.707 --> 27:06.666
It's just two apartments per floor?

27:06.834 --> 27:10.795
- You didn't tell them about it?
- It can speak for itself.

27:12.172 --> 27:13.631
Voilà.

27:19.054 --> 27:21.097
Oh, my God.

27:22.016 --> 27:24.309
It's what they call a Classic Eight.

27:24.476 --> 27:27.312
Be careful. I don't have a map.
I don't want you to get lost.

27:27.479 --> 27:31.691
We had them paint it white. Let you see it
naked before you pick your palette.

27:31.859 --> 27:32.942
What am I picking?

27:33.110 --> 27:34.444
Palette. Your colors.

27:34.611 --> 27:36.279
Oh, yes.

27:38.198 --> 27:40.241
I need to warn you about one thing.

27:40.409 --> 27:44.495
There are going to be some
very envious people down at the firm.

27:44.663 --> 27:48.166
There aren't many of these apartments.
They're a partner's perk.

27:48.334 --> 27:50.626
You must've made quite an impression.

27:50.794 --> 27:54.714
Oh, my God, three bedrooms.
You know what that means?

27:54.882 --> 27:56.215
Babies.

27:56.383 --> 28:00.511
- It took us six years to get in here.
- Oh, wow.

28:02.848 --> 28:05.141
Unbelievable.

28:06.101 --> 28:07.643
- Thank you very much.
- Jackie.

28:07.853 --> 28:09.479
Kevin.

28:12.316 --> 28:14.692
Are you really this good?

28:15.444 --> 28:16.611
I sure as hell hope so.

28:18.280 --> 28:20.239
They must want you pretty bad.

28:22.242 --> 28:23.868
Look, Mar...

28:24.328 --> 28:27.497
I'm only getting behind this
if you're on board.

28:27.664 --> 28:29.665
If you want to go home...

28:29.833 --> 28:31.542
I'm with you.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.211
Sure.

28:33.379 --> 28:36.714
Let's go back to Gainesville,
back to the condo.

28:36.882 --> 28:40.843
You keep scrounging for clients and
I'll keep repossessing cars for Akamian.

28:41.011 --> 28:44.764
And maybe, just maybe,
if we kill ourselves...

28:44.932 --> 28:50.103
in about five years we can afford a baby
and a weekend shack at Gulf Shores.

28:50.729 --> 28:52.897
Are you shitting me?

28:58.612 --> 28:59.862
I love you.

29:00.030 --> 29:02.198
I love you too.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.829
Tadashi Osumi, Media.

29:07.996 --> 29:10.498
Walter Krasna, Maritime Law.

29:10.666 --> 29:12.125
Bashir Toabal, Energy Law.

29:12.292 --> 29:14.043
I run the Islamic subgroup.

29:14.211 --> 29:17.171
Joyce Rensaleer,
Mergers and Acquisitions.

29:17.339 --> 29:19.841
Eddie Barzoon, Managing Director...

29:20.676 --> 29:21.926
and Real Estate.

29:22.136 --> 29:25.096
Pradeed Resh, Intellectual Properties.

29:25.264 --> 29:28.391
Christabella Andrioli,
International Trade and Customs...

29:28.559 --> 29:30.852
EC and G7.

29:32.771 --> 29:34.313
There it is, Kevin.

29:34.481 --> 29:36.149
The whole team.

29:36.316 --> 29:39.360
Welcome to Milton,
Chadwick and Waters.

29:39.528 --> 29:42.488
So, what do you think?
You can change the furniture if you like.

29:42.656 --> 29:44.157
I guess it'll do.

29:44.324 --> 29:45.992
Until something better comes along?

29:46.160 --> 29:47.910
Kevin Lomax, Pam Garrety.

29:48.078 --> 29:49.787
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

29:49.997 --> 29:52.248
Pam was at the Brooklyn DA's office
14 years...

29:52.416 --> 29:54.876
so she knows her way
around the local scene.

29:55.085 --> 29:57.170
You'll expedite his bar application?

29:57.379 --> 30:00.465
It's in the pipeline.
For now, you'll work pro hac vice.

30:00.632 --> 30:03.176
I petitioned Florida
for a letter of good conduct.

30:03.343 --> 30:07.430
And I prepared, at Mr. Milton's request,
an overview of the Moyez case.

30:07.598 --> 30:08.848
The Moyez case?

30:10.434 --> 30:11.976
Move, move, move!

30:33.874 --> 30:35.041
What do you think?

30:35.209 --> 30:38.002
It's a health-code case and it's a loser.

30:40.005 --> 30:41.672
So, what's the point?

30:41.840 --> 30:46.093
He wants to see if I'll plea-bargain.
It's a test, right?

30:46.261 --> 30:48.221
Isn't everything?

30:49.932 --> 30:52.600
It's an 18th-century Italian silk damask...

30:52.768 --> 30:56.687
with an embossed floriated pattern
of undulating acanthus leaves.

30:56.855 --> 30:58.523
Lovely, isn't it?

31:00.108 --> 31:02.485
And this is about what?

31:02.653 --> 31:04.237
The price?

31:04.404 --> 31:07.949
Oh, it's about 2000 a panel.

31:08.116 --> 31:11.494
We'll take it. At 1400.

31:11.662 --> 31:13.746
You made it.

31:13.914 --> 31:15.373
Hey, baby.

31:15.541 --> 31:17.458
I thought you said it was impossible.

31:17.626 --> 31:20.336
I thought you said it was important.

31:26.426 --> 31:27.552
Go get them.

31:27.761 --> 31:29.512
Go get them, man.

31:29.721 --> 31:32.098
Tell him, "Cut that shit down."

31:32.266 --> 31:36.185
I know what they're doing over there.
That's right.

31:36.353 --> 31:40.147
Tell him, "Take all that noise
back to Africa."

31:49.241 --> 31:53.536
Good afternoon.
I'm looking for Philippe Moyez.

32:04.715 --> 32:07.216
Look, I'm not sure
I'm making myself clear.

32:07.426 --> 32:10.970
Moyez, you need him?
To speak with him?

32:11.138 --> 32:13.055
Show him your boots.

32:15.142 --> 32:17.810
You're saying he's down here
in the basement?

32:18.395 --> 32:19.437
In the dark?

32:19.646 --> 32:22.773
Where do you think I'm taking you?
Ha, ha.

32:32.367 --> 32:34.619
I thought I would recognize you...

32:36.204 --> 32:37.913
but I do not.

32:39.291 --> 32:41.083
Mr. Moyez?

32:42.669 --> 32:44.503
We've never met.

32:44.838 --> 32:47.840
I'm Kevin Lomax. I'm a lawyer.

32:48.342 --> 32:50.801
I'm here about the animals.

32:51.928 --> 32:55.806
We have an investment in blood.

32:56.683 --> 32:58.976
Think of it as spiritual currency.

33:00.771 --> 33:03.314
Spiritual currency.

33:04.858 --> 33:08.027
Look, Mr. Moyez,
I'm going to need your help with this.

33:13.200 --> 33:15.117
What is the name of the man...

33:15.327 --> 33:17.995
who will prosecute us?

33:18.163 --> 33:19.664
Merto.

33:19.831 --> 33:23.376
Assistant District Attorney Arnold Merto.

33:27.881 --> 33:30.049
What are you doing, Mr. Moyez?

33:30.217 --> 33:33.427
With this tongue, we create silence.

33:33.595 --> 33:35.137
You can go now.

33:35.305 --> 33:37.056
You will have all the help...

33:37.224 --> 33:39.266
I can give you...

33:39.434 --> 33:41.477
against Monsieur Merto.

33:49.361 --> 33:51.696
It's arbor green. What do you think?

33:52.823 --> 33:55.074
Not with your complexion.

33:59.413 --> 34:01.205
New York City health codes.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.792
- That's all of it?
- Not quite.

34:09.089 --> 34:10.840
Thanks.

34:14.678 --> 34:16.303
Caribbean green.

34:17.472 --> 34:19.306
Something cooler, maybe. Cooler.

34:19.474 --> 34:21.308
A cooler green.

34:24.103 --> 34:26.272
Too institutional.

34:26.940 --> 34:28.190
I love green.

34:28.358 --> 34:33.487
I love it but it's one thing to wear it
and another to have it on your walls.

34:35.782 --> 34:40.077
I'm just trying to help. It's your walls.
Do what you want.

34:42.664 --> 34:45.958
Remember, it's only a health-code case.

34:46.126 --> 34:47.543
Good night.

35:06.938 --> 35:11.817
This is the first time since I've
been 13 years old I don't have a job...

35:11.985 --> 35:13.694
or two.

35:13.862 --> 35:16.489
I feel like I'm floating around
in that place.

35:16.656 --> 35:19.241
You know, just drifting around
or something.

35:20.952 --> 35:23.204
You'll settle in.

35:23.663 --> 35:26.081
We had this little office in the condo...

35:26.249 --> 35:27.374
- Thanks.
- Mm-hm.

35:27.542 --> 35:31.670
You know, his side and my side.
Real nice.

35:31.838 --> 35:35.758
At night, I'd go to sleep,
I'd see that light on...

35:37.803 --> 35:39.970
If I want to see Leamon...

35:40.138 --> 35:41.889
I make an appointment.

35:47.312 --> 35:50.356
You're kidding, right?

35:53.944 --> 35:55.903
God, how do you handle it?

35:56.071 --> 35:58.364
Take a look around, honey.

35:58.532 --> 36:01.242
Look, you've got three choices.

36:01.409 --> 36:03.494
The Holy Trinity:

36:03.662 --> 36:05.746
You can work...

36:06.373 --> 36:08.290
you can play...

36:09.125 --> 36:10.793
or you can breed.

36:12.045 --> 36:14.171
That's a veal roast, Your Honor.

36:14.339 --> 36:17.424
USDA approved and stamped.

36:17.592 --> 36:20.511
Men kill animals and eat their flesh.

36:20.679 --> 36:23.639
Philippe Moyez killed a goat.

36:24.140 --> 36:26.016
He killed a goat.

36:26.309 --> 36:28.519
And he did it at home...

36:28.687 --> 36:32.815
in a manner consistent
with his religious beliefs.

36:32.983 --> 36:35.734
Now, Mr. Merto may find that bizarre.

36:37.112 --> 36:40.739
It's certainly not a religious practice
performed by everyone.

36:40.907 --> 36:42.825
It's not as common as, say...

36:42.993 --> 36:44.577
circumcision.

36:44.744 --> 36:46.954
It's not as common as the belief that...

36:47.122 --> 36:50.207
wine transforms into blood.

36:50.375 --> 36:54.545
Some people handle poisonous snakes
to prove their faith.

36:54.713 --> 36:57.256
Some people walk on fire.

36:57.424 --> 36:59.216
Philippe Moyez killed a goat.

36:59.384 --> 37:01.051
And he did it...

37:01.303 --> 37:05.180
while observing
his constitutionally protected...

37:05.348 --> 37:06.390
religious beliefs.

37:08.351 --> 37:12.062
Your Honor, this case
is not about keeping goats...

37:12.230 --> 37:15.649
or transporting goats or goat licensing.

37:15.817 --> 37:19.653
The city was less concerned
with the care of the animals...

37:19.821 --> 37:22.197
than the manner with which
they were slaughtered.

37:22.365 --> 37:23.657
Objection!

37:23.825 --> 37:26.493
Okay. Enough, enough. I got it.

37:26.661 --> 37:28.203
Let's wrap it up.

37:28.371 --> 37:29.997
Your Honor...

37:30.540 --> 37:33.334
the city timed this police action
to catch my client...

37:33.543 --> 37:38.088
exercising his constitutionally
protected right to religious freedom.

37:38.256 --> 37:40.716
This is a law protecting
kosher butchering.

37:40.884 --> 37:42.426
Exactly, Your Honor.

37:42.594 --> 37:45.971
I'd like to move at this time
for a verdict of dismissal.

37:46.139 --> 37:49.808
I happen to know a little bit
about kashruth law, Mr. Lomax.

37:49.976 --> 37:51.644
I'm aware of that, Your Honor.

37:51.811 --> 37:55.272
That's why I feel confident
in requesting a dismissal.

37:56.191 --> 37:57.232
Mr. Merto?

37:59.736 --> 38:02.738
- Your Honor...
- Mr. Merto.

38:03.990 --> 38:05.699
For God's sake, man...

38:13.833 --> 38:16.543
- Congratulations. Great job.
- Thanks.

38:16.711 --> 38:20.381
Bravo! Bravo!

38:20.548 --> 38:22.967
Pamela, you look lovely.

38:23.134 --> 38:24.176
So, Philippe...

38:24.344 --> 38:25.511
satisfied?

38:25.679 --> 38:27.596
Always, Jean.

38:27.764 --> 38:28.847
Kevin.

38:29.057 --> 38:30.933
What can I say?

38:32.018 --> 38:34.311
Outstanding.

38:34.479 --> 38:37.439
Go figure it, a guy like Moyez...

38:37.607 --> 38:39.942
living in some subterranean shithole...

38:40.151 --> 38:44.029
all the while he's walking around
with $15 million in the bank.

38:44.197 --> 38:45.614
You're kidding.

38:45.782 --> 38:48.200
What do you think he's paying us in?
Goat's blood?

38:48.410 --> 38:52.371
Tarzan, we're billing you out
at 400 an hour, my friend.

38:52.539 --> 38:55.916
I don't see a whole lot of pro-bono work
in your immediate future.

38:56.084 --> 38:59.044
I figured you came down to make sure
I didn't fuck this up.

38:59.254 --> 39:01.046
Maybe I did.

39:01.214 --> 39:04.591
Don't get too cocky, my boy.
No matter how good you are...

39:04.801 --> 39:07.636
don't let them see you coming.
That's the gaffe, my friend.

39:07.804 --> 39:09.888
You've gotta keep yourself small.

39:10.098 --> 39:11.181
Innocuous.

39:11.474 --> 39:12.808
Be the little guy.

39:13.018 --> 39:15.227
You know, the nerd, the leper...

39:15.395 --> 39:18.397
the shitkicking surfer. Look at me.

39:20.233 --> 39:22.943
Underestimated from day one.

39:23.403 --> 39:26.864
You'd never think I was
a master of the universe, would you?

39:27.866 --> 39:30.784
That's your only weakness,
as far as I can see.

39:30.994 --> 39:32.161
What's that?

39:32.620 --> 39:34.246
It's the look.

39:34.622 --> 39:37.207
That Florida stud thing. What is that?

39:37.375 --> 39:40.210
Excuse me, ma'am.
Did I leave my boots under your bed?

39:41.588 --> 39:43.589
Never worked a jury that didn't have
a woman.

39:43.757 --> 39:45.340
You know what you're missing?

39:45.508 --> 39:47.593
You're missing what I have.

39:48.053 --> 39:52.347
There's this beautiful girl,
just fucked me 40 ways from Sunday...

39:52.515 --> 39:56.101
we're done, she's walking
to the bathroom, trying to walk...

39:56.269 --> 39:57.853
she turns...

39:58.021 --> 39:59.646
she looks...

39:59.814 --> 40:01.607
it's me.

40:01.775 --> 40:05.194
Not the Trojan army that just fucked her.
Little old me.

40:06.071 --> 40:07.863
She gets this look on her face like:

40:08.031 --> 40:10.199
"How the hell did that happen?"

40:12.368 --> 40:15.412
I'm the hand up Mona Lisa's skirt.

40:16.039 --> 40:17.998
I'm a surprise, Kevin.

40:18.166 --> 40:20.125
They don't see me coming.

40:20.293 --> 40:21.794
That's what you're missing.

40:21.961 --> 40:24.213
- Where's the chicken?
- What?

40:36.309 --> 40:38.811
There's a chicken, plays tic-tac-toe...

40:38.978 --> 40:41.772
never loses. He's famous.

40:43.525 --> 40:45.734
Never loses, like you.

40:45.902 --> 40:47.319
Tic-tac-toe.

40:47.487 --> 40:49.655
Come on. I'll show you
the fastest way uptown.

40:49.864 --> 40:52.699
Learn the subways, Kevin.

40:53.118 --> 40:54.535
Use them.

40:54.702 --> 40:56.745
Stay in the trenches.

